                             <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub51.ezboard.com/bstormmountain.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=yakov>Yakov</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>All-weather Mountaineer</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#333333>(2/27/02 12:56:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub51.ezboard.com/fstormmountainfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=83.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Checking In</span><hr size=1> Doom, listen.<br>
<br>
I think she didn't leave because she wanted 'bigger and better'. I think she left simply because she felt overwhelmed. I left because a large portion of my friends have, and SM no longer feels the same. My loyalty is to my friends personally, and I hope you remain one, not to the guild itself.<br>
<br>
I am not moving on to bigger things. I am considering joining a guild an old friend is in, but at the same time, I may very well go solo. You have every right to be angry at me, but I certainly hope you aren't. Sonnya's case was probably very similar to my own. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub51.ezboard.com/ulochlannsm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>LochlannSM</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>All-weather Mountaineer</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#333333>(2/27/02 3:10:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub51.ezboard.com/fstormmountainfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=83.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Checking In</span><hr size=1> I think the link below describes what happens to those who DON'T take breaks from EQ here and there, and the whole &quot;bigger and better&quot; thing that affects a lot of us sometimes..and can make us think of the game as &quot;work&quot; and a frustrating experience.<br>
<br>
